  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My uncle was very, very good to him and in many, many ways, and he worked for him until he became sick in 1960.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So he was there for almost 20 years that he-- well, not quite 20 years. 15, 17 years, in his chosen field doing what he knew to do.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In fact, on one occasion in 1949 he-- my uncle sent him to Europe on a buying trip, at which point he made contact with his old colleagues in Belgium and Holland and so forth.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And also on that trip to Europe, he met his older brother who was his partner in business, who was then living in France, in Paris.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And together, they set up a monument on the Jewish cemetery for the members of the family that were deported, and lost, and legally sold the property for which a post-war they-- with Germany being in rubble, it was just pittance, but they didn't want anything to do with-- with Germany.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They just sold it for a few thousand dollars and thought that that was pretty nifty.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And so he worked for my uncle, and that was a very, very good arrangement.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I went to plod on through school, still dreaming perhaps someday to do something with medicine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I knew I couldn't afford a medical school, but I always thought, well, there must be a branch or something that I'm going to be able to afford.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I saved money fastidiously for babysitting jobs, like $0.25 a week for sitting every night, doing dishes, and ironing, and all kinds of things for my babies.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, putting a little money-- a little of my money went to the family to help support, to pay for the combined expenses of the family, and I did anything.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
